&lt;p&gt;The&lt;strong&gt; Loan Processor&lt;/strong&gt; supports multiple loan officers that specialize in anything&amp;nbsp;from a simple unsecured loan to a complex commercial real estate loan, and&amp;nbsp;everything in between. To help loan officers provide reliable, consistent service&amp;nbsp;to the customers, the loan processor responds to a multitude of emails and&amp;nbsp;phone calls, helps loan officers stay in compliance, and works well under&amp;nbsp;pressure and deadlines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you have already achieved: (Requirements)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience in a lending atmosphere with specific knowledge of loan&lt;br&gt;operations/servicing duties and a basic understanding of underwriting guidelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with data entry and Microsoft Office products, LaserPro LOS, Finastra Phoenix&lt;br&gt;Core and ECM imaging&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A precise attention to details&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The motivation to learn and constantly improve skills, processes and tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The people skills required to work with all different types of personalities from various&lt;br&gt;backgrounds&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good judgment and the ability to keep information confidential&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to work with little to no supervision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you are great at: (Responsibilities)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process an application and verify accuracy of information supplied&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare applicable disclosures depending on the loan type&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand and be able to explain disclosures and loan process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Order credit report, flood determination, appraisal, survey and title insurance and&lt;br&gt;environmental reports&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review appraisals and title insurance received for issues or concerns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Call insurance companies for insurance quotes or policies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare loan closing documents and send to title company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with attorneys to prepare loan documentation, ensure attorney has all necessary&lt;br&gt;information to ensure best enforceability of loan and bank protection&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fund loan and disburse funds&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform compliance check to ensure appropriate documentation, liens are perfected and file&lt;br&gt;maintenance completed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Answer questions in a timely manner in-person, by phone, email, fax or mail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with loan officer, borrower, realtor and title company to schedule loan closings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in weekly/monthly loan meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with any other requests and projects assigned as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you are motivated by:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A fast pace. We’ve grown exponentially and new team members continue to join our DLP family.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A leadership team that trusts each other, communicates effectively, and is committed to helping team members grow, both personally and professionally.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Visionary, smart, and innovative Leadership. Ours is the kind of leadership you read about, hope to work with, and learn from.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A culture focused on developing and investing in team members - coaching, training, and supporting each other. We have a mantra of “Leaders made here” at DLP, focused on developing and growing leaders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Mission:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DLP Bank - where Dream, Live, Prosper isn&#39;t just our name, it&#39;s our philosophy. Our commitment is to deliver a banking experience that helps you dream bigger, live better, and prosper more.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits and Perks:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&l

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is not just a leadership role — it is an opportunity to build a banking franchise in the Lehigh Valley with lasting impact. As Market President, you will lead DLP Bank’s growth in a market deeply connected to our story, driving loans, deposits, fee-based revenue, and community presence while recruiting and leading a top-flight team. You will serve as the senior leader for the market, responsible for business development, client relationships, market profitability, and operational excellence, while building the momentum needed to open a full-service branch within the next 2–3 years. Backed by deep roots in the region — including a shareholder of the holding company, who was born and raised in the area, and went on to build DLP Capital, a high-growth company founded in Bethlehem, PA — this role offers the chance to combine market leadership, entrepreneurial building, and a mission of transforming lives by the building of thriving communities.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you have already achieved: (Requirements)&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8–10 years of commercial banking and/or bank leadership experience, including foundational or preparatory roles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consistently generated significant new loan and deposit business each year, maintain a sizeable portfolio of relationships you manage directly, with producing manager experience preferred&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree or equivalent combination of education and experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to influence and motivate producers, relationship managers, and senior-level internal and external stakeholders, requiring a high degree of credibility, trust, and professional judgment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven success in securing alignment on key initiatives through complex, senior-level discussions, supported by strong written communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional leadership, communication, interpersonal, problem-solving, and decision-making abilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In-depth knowledge of banking products, services, and regulatory requirements, along with advanced analytical, underwriting, and credit risk assessment expertise.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational skills with the ability to manage multiple priorities, meet deadlines, and proactively drive projects to completion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to perform effectively in a fast-paced, high-pressure environment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in operating standard office equipment, including computers, keyboards, telephones, copiers, and calculators.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work at a computer for extended periods (6–8 hours per day as needed).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to work extended hours and travel as required by business needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consistent record of reliable, punctual attendance.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you are great at: (Responsibilities)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong loan, deposit, and fee income generation&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A leader in the local community, well-respected and highly visible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic Leadership &amp;amp; Execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and influence the implementation and achievement of the market’s strategic and operational plans in alignment with DLP Bank’s approved goals and priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate enterprise vision into local market execution, ensuring the loan production office delivers on growth, profitability, service, and operational goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive continuous improvement in market performance, service delivery, and operational processes.&lt;/li&gt;
